arch:property.oc:show_val: Locus 7 is the layer of collapse (Munsell 10 YR 4/3 brown) in the ‘colonnaded corridor.’ It is a loose silt-sand with architectural collapse, stones, pottery, and plaster inclusions. Part of the main collapse of the Bath Complex, it is phased to Stage 6.
2.97 m north south -by- 12.35 m east west.

Phase XI: Further collapse post-CE 5th c., possibly the result of the earthquake of 512. Fill accumulates following the disuse of the canalization systems. The remains of two bodies are found in the upper level fluvial deposits. Localized burning in some areas.
